Provenance
================================================================================

All source code in this repository is original / clean-room work by the EAP
maintainer. NO third-party source code is included or vendored.

The following projects are credited for CONCEPTS and design (no code taken):

  * graphify  — https://github.com/Graphify-Labs/graphify  — MIT
    EAP-Context is an independent, standard-library-only symbol-graph engine
    whose design is informed by graphify's code-graph approach. No graphify
    source and none of its dependencies (tree-sitter, networkx, numpy, etc.)
    are used.

  * context-mode — https://github.com/mksglu/context-mode — Elastic License 2.0
    EAP-Runtime is an independent clean-room reimplementation of the general
    context-offload pattern (also seen in OpenAI Code Interpreter and
    Anthropic's "code execution with MCP"). It contains NO context-mode source.

  * caveman (MIT, Julius Brussee), TLDR (MIT, jqbit), ponytail (MIT, Dietrich
    Gebert) — EAP-Voice descends from TLDR (which credits caveman); ponytail's
    code-brevity concept is an optional Voice sub-mode. No ponytail code taken.

See docs/legal/ATTRIBUTION.md for the full record and the clean-room guard.
